## System Requirements

- Linux (primary supported platform)
- Windows (binary builds available)

---

## Installation

Binaries and source code are available here:

http://sourceforge.net/projects/cfmesh/

---

## Building from Source (Optional)

cfMesh can be built with recent versions of OpenFOAM and foam-extend.

### Requirements

- Working OpenFOAM environment
- Compiler with OpenMP support:
  - GCC ≥ 4.2.4
  - MinGW (Windows, experimental)

⚠️ These instructions are primarily for Linux. Windows users are encouraged to use prebuilt binaries.

### Build

    ./Allwmake

---

## Getting Started

Copy tutorial cases into your OpenFOAM run directory:

    cp -r tutorials $FOAM_RUN

Run the first example:

    cd $FOAM_RUN/tutorials/asmoOctree
    cartesianMesh

Each case includes helper scripts:

- Allrun – runs the case
- Allclean – cleans generated files

